# Evaluate qmd as the Brain Knowledge-Recall Projection

## Question

Joel flagged [tobi/qmd](https://github.com/tobi/qmd): local hybrid search
(SQLite FTS5 + sqlite-vec + RRF + local reranker, MCP server, TS SDK) over
markdown directories. Spike: does it become the KNOWLEDGE projection —
semantic recall over brain roots + observations — likely superseding
add-observation-embeddings (Typesense stays the STREAM projection: run
chunks, session scans)? Doctrine fit is exact: sqlite index in ~/.cache is
rebuildable, files stay truth, collections map to brain-roots.json.

Receipts wanted: install, collections over the three registered roots with
`**/*.svx` globs, `qmd query` receipts including the semantic query lexical
search misses ("what did we decide about memory compression" → the
node-cluster/reflector pages), latency numbers on flagg, MCP smoke test.
